{
    "chapterId": "structures-maintained-throughout-mitosis",
    "title": "Structures maintained throughout mitosis ",
    "pages": [
        {
            "pageId": 47,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "",
                "loop": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "When we look closely at the structures that remain relatively unchanged throughout most of mitosis, they all have prominent localizations to the apical cell-cell contacts. ",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 48,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "examples-of-cell-colonies",
                "loop": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "We can see clearly by visualizing whole colonies with an appropriate rendering algorithm.\n",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 49,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "pull-out-tjp",
                "loop": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "Lets take a closer look at one of these structures, tight junctions.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 50,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "two-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "",
                "loop": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "Tight junctions, labeled in these cells by tagging the protein ZO-1, form cell-cell contacts at the apical surface of the cells and across the epithelial colony.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 51,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "two-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "",
                "loop": true
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "Tight junctions remain localized between cells even as the mitotic cell undergoes massive changes in shape.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 52,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "two-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "",
                "loop": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "This highlights the importance of maintaining the integrity of the epithelial sheet and its barrier function.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 53,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "two-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "",
                "loop": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "Myosin IIB is also necessary for maintaining the integrity of junctions between cells. Therefore, similar to ZO-1, the localization of myosin IIB remains at intercellular junctions throughout mitosis.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 54,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "two-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "",
                "loop": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "However, as cells begin mitosis, myosin 2b also localizes to the cell cortex and later concentrates at the cleavage furrow, a structure responsible for pinching the dividing cell into two.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 55,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "two-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "",
                "loop": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "Thus, myosin is an example of a protein involved in one structure that does not change (the intercellular junction), and a temporary structure that forms only during one part of mitosis.Â ",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
    ]
}